From the Glastonbury Festival, the complete set by the undisputed queen of country
music Dolly Parton from the Pyramid Stage in the now-traditional legends spot on Sunday
afternoon. As the Somerset sunshine shone, and in front of one of the biggest and most
enthusiastic crowds that the Pyramid Stage has ever seen, Dolly performed a rousing
and crowd-pleasing set including self-penned classics such as Jolene, Coat of Many
Colours, 9 to 5, Islands in the Stream and I Will Always Love You. A legendary moment
that the Glastonbury crowd and hopefully Dolly Parton will never forget.
